@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About Us";
}

<head>
        
</head>
<body style="font-family:sans-serif">

    <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-10">
                <h2>Welcome to <b>our world of LEGO,</b></h2>
                <h2>where <b>creativity</b> knows no bounds,</h2>
                <h2>and <b>imagination</b> runs free!</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-2">
                <div class="image-container" style="height: 150px; overflow: hidden;">
                    <img src="~/img/girl.png" alt="Create" class="img-fluid" style="width: auto; height: 100%;">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>


    <hr />

    <div style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:large">
        <div class="image-container" style="width: 100%; height: 80px; overflow: hidden;">
            <img src="~/img/create.png" alt="Create" class="img-fluid" style="object-fit: cover; height: 100%;">
        </div>
        <p>
            Every great journey starts with a single brick, and for Aurora Blackwell, it began in the quiet corner of her living room,
            surrounded by colorful LEGO pieces. Aurora's fascination with LEGO wasn't just about following instructions to build a set;
            it was about seeing beyond the manual, imagining worlds where each brick contributed to the narrative. Her childhood passion
            for LEGO blossomed into a lifelong love affair, with each build more intricate and meaningful than the last. For Aurora,
            LEGO was more than a hobby—it was a way to express her creativity, to challenge herself, and most importantly, to reconnect
            with the joyous simplicity of creating something from nothing.
        </p>

        <div class="image-container" style="width: 100%; height: 80px; overflow: hidden;">
            <img src="~/img/build.png" alt="Create" class="img-fluid" style="object-fit: cover; height: 100%;">
        </div>
        <p>
            The leap from LEGO enthusiast to social media sensation wasn't something Aurora planned. It was her genuine love for the
            craft that she shared on TikTok, one build at a time, that captured hearts worldwide. Her first viral video—a captivating
            time-lapse of an ambitious LEGO build—was a window into her world, where followers could see the patience, skill, and creativity
            involved in each creation. Aurora's TikTok became a platform not just for showcasing her talent but for sharing her journey,
            the ups and downs of creative endeavors, and the endless possibilities LEGO offered. Her move to TikTok was driven by a desire
            to connect with others who shared her passion and to demonstrate that LEGO is a medium for artists, storytellers, and dreamers of all ages.
        </p>

        <div class="image-container" style="width: 100%; height: 80px; overflow: hidden;">
            <img src="~/img/inspire.png" alt="Create" class="img-fluid" style="object-fit: cover; height: 100%;">
        </div>
        <p>
            Today, Aurora's goal extends beyond creating viral content. She aims to inspire. Through her website and her team, Aurora is dedicated
            to building a community where LEGO enthusiasts, both young and old, can find a sense of belonging. She believes in empowering others to
            see the potential in every LEGO brick and set—to understand that within each piece lies the opportunity to build something new and extraordinary.
            Aurora and her team are committed to providing not just a platform to purchase LEGO sets but a space to share ideas, celebrate achievements,
            and inspire each other to build, create, and dream bigger. For Aurora, inspiring others to pick up their first LEGO brick and start their own
            journey of discovery is the ultimate accomplishment.
        </p>
    </div>
    

</body>